      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 35:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ashur (Heb., Ash-hur) means “man of Hur”—that is, the chief of the clan of the Hurites, settled at Ephrath or Bethlehem (1Chronicles 2:19). Comp. Ashbel “man of Bel.” (Ash is the elder form of Ish “man”; as appears from the Phenician inscriptions.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Ashur",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Heb., ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Ash-hur",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") means “man of Hur”—that is, the chief of the clan of the Hurites, settled at Ephrath or Bethlehem (",
            "children": []
