          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " “man”; as appears from the Phenician inscriptions.)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That “Caleb” in this verse means the house of Caleb is evident if we consider that the genealogy makes him great grandson of Judah, whereas the individual Caleb son of Jephunneh took part in the conquest of Canaan, more than four centuries after Judah went down to Egypt.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "That “Caleb” in this verse means the house of Caleb is evident if we consider that the genealogy makes ",
            "children": []
